76561198038753415,Recommended,209670,31260777,Posted: 20 April,all,Mrgrimm150,"Cortex command is a strange case. It reminds me a lot of old PC games like Liero. I think the first thing to make clear is the game is not fun without mods.  The vanilla factions, whilst fun for a while are lacking in many ways and the stuff the community comes up with is much more interesting.The game has some great unique gameplay though. You control a brain, your brain and can use it to control bodies and craft that are called in from space. The game is a weird hybrid of RTS, Side scrolling shooter and Physics puzzler. Each body you control has physics and weight (giving them more weapons makes em heavier) lighter bodies can fly easier but will also die when colliding with concrete at high speed. Heavier bodies can't fly as well but the concrete will get smashed before their faces. The game also has a base building aspect (in some modes) where you put together a 'brain bunker' from various bits and pieces and defend it from people who do not like your brain. Throw in a few mods and the strange physics and unique gameplay make for a highly entertaining experiance....until it crashes.Cortex command is far from stable. It'll crash regularly once you get a few mods going and the loading time when booting up the game does make every crash a tragedy.All things said though I reccomend the game if you can get it on sale. Grab a few mods (I reccomend void wanderers and a few compatible factions to go with it) and have fun shouting at a crash test dummy to stop shooting the doors."
