76561198037070834,Not Recommended,209670,9368803,"Posted: 6 March, 2014",all,Jimbos,"When I first grabbed the game, I was expecting so much more. I had watched videos and done a little bit of research, and the game simply looked amazing for what it was. A unique side scrolling take on RTS.When I actually got to hop in the game however, things went bad fast.First off, learning the controls, even with the assistance of the tutorial was a pain. They only explain the bare minimum in how you can switch out to other units under your influence, and how to control them on a basic level. They tell you nothing of how you're supposed to actually use the unit, or how to activate its various AI scripts and what they actually do. The UI is bare minimum, you have to dig and test everything out on your own just to figure out things that should be presented directly, or have better in game descriptions.While actually controlling your units, you'll find they are slow and terribly clunky. Even the faster/lighter units feel that way, and there's simply no way around. Heavy units are a literal nightmare to move around the map. With heavier units you'll find it almost impossible to reach certain areas, forcing you to use easily killed light units for everything, and only equipping them with the absolute bare minimum to assault the enemy. Attempting to use the AI scripts usually just forces them to saunter off to their deaths, they end up firing into the air blindly or never returning fire, while the enemy computer controlled units decimate your forces from half a mile away with a pistol.While all the equipment and units you can call down are interesting, you'll find yourself most times just calling down basic units due to the cost to protect yourself, while the opponent seems to have near infinite resources he can call on. Even when you have a ton of money it seems to run out in seconds, where there's seem to have no end, even on the easier settings. That and the fact you'll notice the enemy AI is quite crafty in going after your controller unit/brain. Assassinating him from impossible angles, or simply just scuicide bum rushing you, while your idiot AI forces stand there and watch slack jawed, even is they are on sentry/defense mode.There are a number of mods out there that can expand the gameplay, adding modes, areas, new factions and weapons and other things. Some of them are quite excellent, and it's to bad there was such a great modding community for this game, but the developer half♥♥♥♥♥♥♥it for about 10 years. Yep, that's right. This game was 10 years in development before seeing a ""full"" version launch. Looking at the game now you'd probably be wondering where the full version is. It feels much more like a late alpha build, or very early beta.Like I said, it's such a shame there was such a passionate modding community, their talents and time went to waste on a devolper and his half♥♥♥♥♥♥♥game, when the modders could have put their attentions elsewhere and made something amazing in a game people actually care about.If you can get the game for dirt cheap on sale for like 90% off go for it. Simply to check it out, and see ""what could have been"". The potential you can see in videos and in the game itself is amazing. But, the deveolper simply never capitilized on it, and now it sits as pretty much abandonware, festering here on Steam, where the deveolper is still asking money for a dead and rotting corpse of a product he will never patch, update, touch, or even look at again.If the source code gets released, and others pick it up and do something with it, the results might just be amazing. So keep your eyes open if or when that happens.Until then, stay away from this festering pile of abandonware garbage."
