,Recommended,209670,10927033,"Posted: 28 June, 2014",all,JayeStrike,"The first time I heard about this game, the friend who mentioned it to me described it as a cross between Worms and Terraria.  While I don't know if that's the bast analogy, this game certainly brings the best of both genres to the table.  There is a constantly changing battlefield that doesn't reset all the holes and debris just because the fight ends for the day.  There's also an element of creating a safe shelter to direct the operation from, as the whole fight hinges on success or failure in keeping safe one particular member of your forces.I should also point out that in my opinion, CC is not a game about tactical fighting.  Yes, you did just read me deny the majority of standing opinion.  AI can be used for most battle functions that the player can direct, granted not as efficiently as a skilled cortex operator - but no AI can manage your funds.  This game is about war economy.  Deciding what's necessary for an attack and implementing those choices, while keeping back enough money to create a defense.  Bring your management skills: all transactions may just be gold dust but you have to operate a stable system of income and expense to dominate the resource race."
