76561198155102929,Recommended,209670,31664212,Posted: 10 May,all,Ghost993514,"Ok... so... all of you with compatibility issues, I don't see why.It would help to, you know, check the crash log, send it and a message to the dev, and knowing your OS.So I invalidate a lot of those 'negative' reviews.Ok, so this is a review, not a tangent.So, before I buy a game, I get it by 'other means.' Usually, as an extended demo, so I can really see if I like a game or not.If I like it, I buy it. If I don't, I don't buy it, and since I don't like it, get rid of it.I liked this game enough to wait for it to be max price before buying it; mainly to support the dev.But that's saying something.(This'll be primarily based off of the metagame, which is, in this game, a randomly generated sandbox campaign.)Anyways, this game is basically a 2-D construction and combat sandbox, in a more literal sense of the word.You basically have these things called 'brains' which are essentially command units. How you have more than one, I don't know, but you don't have an actual body because humanity 'evolved' past it.So, you have to protect these brain units, while killing the enemy brain, in order to win.Then you dig in, build your base/bunker, and wait for them to attack.However, to win, you need the most gold. In order to get gold, you need 'sites.'You need to manage between these, bulding, attacking, defending, etc.If you're not Control+R (ing) each mission, it's somewhat difficult, because anything can happen. You can either die upon entering, or a random explosion may occur above your brain, or you may get attacked and realize all too late.The only issue is performance, but it's better now. Better...The only other downside other than that, I think, is the lack to choose what you attack with. It randomly assigns weapons and troops on either rocket type and I often find myself annoyed with what I get. I often send my rockets back before they even land, if I can.I don't think changing difficulty does much, though. I know changing 'actor' skill changes accuracy but that's it.It also has a very unique setting, and the lore is pretty interesting if you read up on it."
