,Recommended,209670,33324654,Posted: 6 July,all,Whac-A-Mole Jutsu,"Cortex Command is a game that has the player as a disembodied brain that can take control of units dropped from space in order to complete numerous tasks, such as destroying an enemy brain, defending a base, or playing a game of Keepie-Uppie with a rocket. The game is coded in Lua, and the developers encourage modding, and mods are what make this game shine. Even though the community is slowly releasing few mods, the older, bigger mods might as well be a part of the game, as they have few bugs, and are massive in scope.One of the biggest things that sets this apart from other games like it is the complete lack of online multiplayer, yet with four player local multiplayer, and it works perfectly. The game can be played with a keyboard and mouse, the numberpad, and two controllers.The other big thing that sets it apart from all games is... Crab Bombs. A magical weapon of mass destruction that can do anything from killing everything (including you) to crashing the game, as well as your computer.TL;DR: 8/10, modding is easy and encouraged, local multiplayer instead of online, Crab Bombs are fun."
