,Recommended,209670,22207331,"Posted: 2 April, 2016",all,Dyantier,"Note: I've played well over 300 hours in this game offline and off-steam in the 5 years I've been playing.I highly recommend this game to anyone who enjoys fun games with a bit of strategy.Serving suggestion: This game is best served with a 3 gigabyte helping of mods. These can be found on the workshop.GAMEPLAYYou play on a 2D sideview map usually with your brain and the enemy's brain having to dig gold and purchase different 'actors' to be delivered from orbit for you to use to attempt to destroy the enemy brain.The physics in this game are very detailed and very important to winning. However, it may also be the thing that turns some people off. It makes movement feel somewhat 'heavy' and can be frustrating to get the hang of. But once you figure it out you'll be flying (yes everyone gets a jet pack) the body of your recently de-limbed trooper into the face of the enemy, hopefully decapitating them with the force... or maybe knocking the gun out of their hand... or the enemy might just laugh and shoot your face off.All in all this style is easy to understand and very fun to execute due to the large amount of actors and equipment you can choose from. However some things like the grappling gun and repeller gun are not very useful or practical in normal games.STORYNot much here. We're a bunch of space brains with unlimited armies at our backs that are ready and willing to blast each other for gold.GRAPHICSThe graphical style is wonderfuly done pixel art that isn't to pixely and is pixely enough it doesn't look cheap. It has just the right amount of detail to fantasticaly render every body part and machine piece as they explode and pile up on the map.CONCLUSIONThis is definently THE funnest game I have ever played in my life. The entertainment value is endless due to the active modding community and making mods yourself isn't that hard. It certainly won't disappoint if you can get used to the controls."
