,Recommended,209670,32543361,Posted: 18 June,all,Spiderzo,"First, i would like to start off with a few questions.Have you ever wanted to see a rocket being thrown across a planet, then hitting one of your soldiers' head off?Have you ever wanted to build a base, filled with sentries only so it would end up in a complete mess?Ever wanted to go climbing gibbed bodies?If you answered yes to all or some, then Cortex Command is the game for you!I might be quite late with this review, but to the people who have never heard about this amazing game; Or were thinking about playing it;Cortex Command is a 2D shooter & strategy game in one; Where everything is possible.Note though, it's not exactly for the eyes. The graphics are fine, but not overly complicated.It's mostly focused on physics than graphics. Which, in my personal opinion, is so much more fun.You can quite literally move, create and destroy every single pixel in the game.Don't let my hours of game-time fool you. It's a great game.If you're still not convinced though, let me talk about the story/gameplay options.You take the role of one (or more) brains, and in the metagame, your mission is to take over areas, and defeat the enemies. All in the meantime, you have to manage your money (gold) to not run out, because then you're basicallyscrewed.Actually, you can dig out gold ores in certain areas to immediately gain some money.However, a Metagame can take a long time. Considering if you're building your own bases (which you can do), grinding up money from areas, taking your time in battles.. you get the idea. It's a long time.If you're not into that, or perhaps you are a busy person, you can easily go into a scenario battle, and mess around.Make small battles, or gigantic wars at your heart's desire.. and i still haven't mentioned the mods!Boy would i go on forever.The modding community in this game is amazing. Starting from the half-life combine tech, all the way to the Gears of War weapons. Guess what? Even YOU can make mods! It ain't that difficult if you look into it a bit more.Though i must warn you, too many actors; or older PCs may lag, as this is a heavily physics & AI based game. Just throwin' it out there.Honestly, it's worth your money, as long you're into 2D Chaos & Strategy, and you're not looking for realistic graphics, but rather, for hella fun gameplay.In conclusion, give this game a 10/10. You definitely should give it a try.Note: Mind my grammar, pretty please? I'll give you a cookie-"
,Recommended,209670,32850553,Posted: 27 June,all,Cortex,"Cortex command is a side-view strategy game in which the goal is to defeat the other players' brain(s) or in some game modes to keep yours alive. The game has multiple factions each with their own weapons and soldiers, the game on its own is fun to play but it gets repetetive after about 20 hours of playing (for me). Where the game really shines is its modding community, if you go to its modding page you will find a hundred or so mods which get updated every so often and sometimes new ones are added as well, for me that made it worth it to play the game for more than 100 hundred hours with friends, the only down sides are that each loaded mod increases loading times by a lot, I have to wait 5 minutes for my game to start and hope I had enabled/disabled the mods I wanted, the other downside is that it can only be played on the same computer or with LAN, no online multiplayer, overall I think this game, its developers and the modding community are awesome."
