,Recommended,209670,30601363,Posted: 18 March,all,Blyatman,"Absolutelly great game with endless funCortex Command is a really REALLY great game. It has the tactical feel of  ""Should i send a squad of riflemen, or a All in One solution thats fragile?"", but when enemy drop pods start crushing your people and when one of your allies ""accidentaly"" shoots a RPG at a friendly dropship you know you are playing this the right way.But what makes it so great?Well then, sit down and let me tell you about the magic of a PHYSICS ENGINE in a 2D enviroment that is always fresh. You can literally use soldiers as a ballistic missile with C4 stuck on them, you can use a super heavy soldier withRocket Propelled Chainsawsto annihilate a squad of enemies while a dismembered, bleeding enemy with a pistol shoots at your back. You can not decline the satisfaction of firing grenades into a bunker and remotely detonating it.Anything else?Well of course. You have the steam workshop with many GREAT mods like Void Wanderer which entirely change the entire point of the game, some mods with OP factions like DsTech with flashy weaponry and high cost. Or maybe if you just wanna mess around Hueg pack of mods with quality content like a nuclear fridge or a walking gas canister.Pros:Provides endless funThe workshop provides quality contentThe physics engine keeps everything fresh and unpredictableFor the amount of particle movement and physics the optimitisation is EXTRAORDINARY goodEasy to mod, create content and overall costumisableIs even more fun in front of a TV with friendsCons:The AI isn`t anything special but can be challengingThe developers are a small, slow team but they still updateThe game is still a bit rough around the edges.All in all. This is one of the most under-rated games on steam that deserves more attention as it is unique and fun as hell.Really, if you can afford a couple of quid, pick this up right away."
