76561198053811458,Recommended,209670,30740668,Posted: 25 March,all,Jerln,"Cortex Command is in a sort of development hell, I think. Updates are very infrequent, so despite it being early access, don't count on it becoming a finished game any time soon.Despite that, it's areally fun game.I can, and have, played the Bunker Breach game mode all day long.It's sort of like those classic tank games, where the terrain is made of little individual particles. However, in this game, everything is made of those little particles. For example, if you got a headshot on one of those orange Dummy robots, their head would fly off of their body. Depending on what you shot them with, it might stay intact and land on the ground, where it is now considered part of the terrain and can be further destroyed. Or, it might land on a rock and shatter into pieces. Or, you might have shot them with something like a giant laser, in which case you probably won't find any part of it at all.It's really in-depth with it's carnage and destruction, is what I'm getting at. Even the bullets are actual projectiles affected by physics- impact strength, ricochets, drop off. This is more noticeable in some weapons, like the Revolver Cannon, which fires chunks of metal a little smaller than a unit's head."
