,Recommended,209670,28835733,"Posted: 30 December, 2016",all,Dave.,"I bought this game on September 30th, 2012, 2 days after it released on Steam, for $17.99.  Since then, I have watched the rating of it drop and watch as the game was dragged through the mud.  I have a tendancy to leave games for a while (especially early access), and try to finish all the games I have that are 'finished', so I can play through everything being complete.  Over the years as well, I have watched as it seemed this game was lost in the void of the oh so many games never coming to fruition for whatever reasons (owning some as well, of course).  It's pretty frustrating, however I played this game once, yup, One time, foralmostan hour, that's my actual playtime.  Yet after all the complaining, and the Steam refund system coming into full effect (which I have used), after thinking this game was lost, and such a small amount of time played, the time I did play, through all the rough edges, I could tell that I would enjoy this game, someday, when I got around to it.  It was only when I left another game today, December 30th, 2016, and became really confused to see Cortex Command at the bottom of my update list, I was happy to see they are not gone.  So here we are, 4 years later, sure it may be some time before I really sit down and get into it, I will say, it does have a certain charm about it, that I could not abandon after all that time, ..is the point.  *To be updated*"
