,Recommended,209670,35489757,Posted: 5 October,all,Liquid Mantis,"Cortex Command is the equivelant of that game you used to play as kid with action figures. The sort of one where you mash two things together and one was ""defeated"". It's good fun, the modding scene is fairly strong and pretty much makes this game even though the Default units are still pretty good. Wanna see the imperium of man go up against the Combine Overwatch? This is your game. Want to drop giant mechs with mixed results onto a heavily fortified base? This is your game. The AI is fairly competent although you'll get the occassional ""DUHHHHH"" from any of the AI trying to mine or brain hunt.It's alot of fun besieging or being sieged, economically dumping crab bombs onto the surface to try and survive and killing yourself in process. It's a great game. I got this back when this was in the humble bundle but i still think the price point applies, it's good fun and i don't think you'll be disappointed.The jank on the controls is there and you need to circumvent it but it was never so much of a problem that it irritated me. It only really annoyed me when units didn't climb stairs or i needed to rely on the jetpack for any form of vertical movement. However, i managed to look past it but others haven't quite clearly."
76561198065842779,Not Recommended,209670,6417155,"Posted: 2 March, 2013",all,d000t,"I really like the gameplay of this game, and local multiplayer is really a lot of fun if you can ever get it to work. Every time I remember this game I want to sit down and play with it but every time I find new bugs and it is really frustrating to play. Controllers sometimes work, I have no idea why they wont work but i have perfectly functional xbox controllers that the game simply doesnt recognise. The game says the right resolution but the resolution obviously isnt right because I am zoomed in to the op left corner of the screen. The Steam Workshop content is pretty good, I just wish I could get this game to work straight away when my friends come over.Personally the only fun gamemodes are wave defence and brain vs brain, but I wish I could save bases Ive built so I can re-use them (and not rebuild them every time)Overall ive probably spent more time searching forums and fiddling with settings and third party programs trying to get this game to work and getting frustrated over glitches than actually playing the game."
